<SubSection title = "Example: bicycle pedaling (reciprocal to rotary)" id = "example_bicycle_pedaling_reciprocal_to_rotary">
        <p>
          Bicycles are an efficient means of human-powered
          transportation due to their use of rotary wheel
          motion. Humans cannot directly produce indefinite rotations,
          however, so some mechanism is required to translate
          reciprocating human motion into rotary motion. Bicycles
          achieve this conversion with two four-bar linkages, each
          consisting of the two segments of the riders leg, the
          bicycle frame, and the <a
          href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crank_(mechanism)">crank</a>,
          as shown below.
        </p>
        <div class="figureContainer width600" id="aml-fb">
          <canvas id="aml-fb-c" width="600" height="400" class="figureImage" >
          </canvas>
          <p class="controls">
